import React,{useState} from "react"
import { AppBar, Box, Tab, Tabs, TextField, Tooltip, Typography } from "@mui/material"

function NavBar() {
    const [value,setValue]=useState(0)
  return (
    <>
      <Box sx={{flexGrow:1}}>
      <AppBar sx={{bgcolor:"yellow",padding:'10px'}}>
        <Tooltip>
            <Typography variant="h6" sx={{float:"left", marginTop:'7px',marginLeft:'10px' ,color:'black'}}>LOGO</Typography>
            <TextField  type='text'  
                placeholder='Search' size="small" 
                sx={{marginLeft:'60px',marginTop:'7px', bgcolor:'#ffff',width:'400px', borderRadius:'4px'}} 
            />
            <Tabs sx={{float:"right"}}
              value={value}
              textColor="pink"
              onChange={(e, val) =>
                setValue(val)
                
              }
            >
                <Tab label='Home' sx={{color:'black'}} value='0'/>
                <Tab label='About' sx={{color:'black'}} value='1'/>
                <Tab label='Contact' sx={{color:'black'}} value='2'/>
                <Tab label='login' variant="contained" sx={{float:"right",marginTop:'5px' ,color:'black'}} value='3'/>
            </Tabs>
                   
        </Tooltip>
      </AppBar>
      </Box>
    </>
  )
}

export default NavBar
